details.description:
Finca Coffee is a coffee shop in the lobby of EastSide Charlotte. Our goal is to provide the best farm-to-cup experience and create a space in the community that has a relaxed vibe perfect for work, study or just catching up with friends.
Need coffee at your event? We can help!

reviews_data.review_text: A little hidden but once you pull into the parking lot they make it easy to find. My coffee was perfectly creamy and smooth you can tell it’s very fresh. This is super convenient because it’s close to my house and I’d rather support a small business over Starbuck’s any day! Thank you!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the review, Kelly! Hope to see you back soon.

reviews_data.review_text: I am hesitant to leave a review but I must…. This place is a vibe. Firstly, the soothing music, the great chai latte, the friendly customer service. Yes, top tier. Also they are faith based, I am in full support! This is a hidden gem and the was perfect for me to get some work done!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind review Cocoa! Glad you enjoyed the chai. Please come back soon.

reviews_data.review_text: One of the only places in Charlotte where you can get a delicious coffee for less than $6! We sat here all morning and were able to get a lot of work done because it was nice & quiet ☺️
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your review, Rebekah. So glad ya'll stopped by!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee shop with great owners!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We appreciate your kind words, Kyle.

reviews_data.review_text: Cortado was a good one today!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Glad you enjoyed the cortado. Come back soon, Nis!

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee was good and staff was very friendly!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you!

reviews_data.review_text:
Brand new place, experienced barista to enjoy well-made latte with oatmilk!
No bakery yet((
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for stopping by and for the review, Vladimir! I am pleased to announce that we have added some delicious pastries to our menu. Thank you for the suggestion.

reviews_data.review_text: Best coffee in town! Ten out of ten, highly recommend.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, Jalen! We appreciate the review. Come back soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
It is a coffee shop inside a church where you can enter from the left side of the main building.

Super cute set up, family owned and very cozy.

Will definitely be coming back to do work when I need a quiet spot.

Only constructive criticism is that they only have one cup size and due to how large it is the latter was diluted a bit.
So a smaller "medium" sized cup ( 6oz) might help.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for the review, Venessa. We will definitely  take that into consideration. Posting with pictures is always a great help!

I do have a suggestion for a drink if you're looking for a less diluted option: a wet cappuccino. There's less milk in that and with it being "wet" it will not be as foamy but closer to latte milk. Give it a shot next time!

reviews_data.review_text: So lucky to have found this gem between legs of my hour commute. An Oasis of friendliness and fantastic coffee. Appreciate you guys, see you soon.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're lucky to have such kind people find us and give us a shot! Come by again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Great atmosphere , I love the people and the coffee! Every time I go I get met with a warm welcome and they always have regulars there talking to me too! Definetly a must go for anybody wanting to try good coffee!
reviews_data.owner_answer: So glad you enjoyed it, sir! Please come back soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Such an amazing small business in Charlotte, NC. The coffee is delicious and these are truly wonderful people!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, Brandon. We're always glad to see you in the shop!

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing Chai latte loved everything, friendly and fast service.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you! We appreciate you stopping by!!!

reviews_data.review_text: Very friendly very nice lovely atmosphere
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the review, Aaron! It was nice seeing you last week. Come back soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee! The fresh ground coffee beans make for a great flavor! Fast, friendly and welcoming atmosphere. Definitely will be coming back! 10/10
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, Rojay!

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome Service!  Awesome coffee!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Easy to do with awesome customers! Thank you for stopping by.

reviews_data.review_text:
Finca Coffee is truly a hidden gem in Charlotte! Brenda and Mauricio have created something special—more than just a coffee shop, it’s a place where you feel at home the moment you step up to the counter. Their passion for quality and community is evident in every cup they serve.

I absolutely love their chai and dirty chai lattes—hands down the best I’ve had! The balance of spices, creaminess, and the perfect hint of sweetness makes it an experience, not just a drink. Whether you’re a coffee lover or just looking for a warm and welcoming place to grab a cup, Finca is the spot.

If you haven’t been yet, do yourself a favor and stop by. You won’t just get a great cup of coffee, you’ll feel like part of the family.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much, John!
